    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Electric, straight-handled irons used for dry mounting photographs by holding paper, dry-mounting tissue, and cardboard in place until they are put in a dry-mounting press, where they are thoroughly bound.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000026701/Mayer, Dictionary of Art Terms and Techniques (1969)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具直立式手把的電子熨斗，用於乾裱照片；可用來將紙張、乾旅膠片以及卡紙固定在乾裱機中進行完全壓裱。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Elektrische ijzers met rechte handvatten die worden gebruikt om foto's droog in te lijsten door het papier, tissue en karton op de plaats te houden totdat ze in de droogpers worden geplaatst waar ze stevig worden vastgezet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
